TI  - Collaborative logistics for agricultural products of 'farmer plus consumer integration purchase' under platform empowerment
AU  - Zhou, Lichen
AU  - Hou, Guisheng
AU  - Rao, Weizhen
T2  - EXPERT SYSTEMS WITH APPLICATIONS
AB  - The platform is a comprehensive digital technology carrier that can facilitate the digitization of sales and make it possible to directly connect farmers and consumers. Multi-owner collaboration in logistics may considerably improve efficiency and sustainability, which is crucial for agricultural logistics. This paper introduces a logistics collaboration mechanism for agricultural products of 'Farmer + Consumer Integration Purchase' based on platform information openness and resource sharing. First, the Multi-owner Collaborative Vehicle Routing Problem with Heterogeneous Fleets and Time Windows (MOHFCVRPTW) model was designed. Second, the developed solution is the Adaptive Large Neighborhood Search Heuristic Algorithm (ALNS), which can solve 2n-1 (n is the number of enterprises) sub-alliances corresponding to the collaborative problem at once and produce the scheme and cost. Third, the Shapley value method is used to design a scientific and reasonable cost-sharing mechanism to allocate the total cost of the alliance to each logistics enterprise. Finally, the validity of the mechanism and the model are verified in the context of real logistics networks in Qingdao and Shanghai, and the profit of farmers is quantified by considering the cost of loss of agricultural products. The research found that the logistics collaboration mechanism has achieved cost savings for logistics enterprises, reduced carbon emissions, and improved transportation timeliness. At the same time, losses on agricultural products have been significantly reduced, and farmers' profits have increased. In addition, with the expansion of the scale of the alliance, the increase in the diversity of transport vehicles, and the improvement in the distribution aggregation degree of farmers, the benefits of the collaborative operation mode are more significant. The platform enables the exchange matching and collaborative transportation of agricultural products rapidly and has significant sustainable benefits, which has guiding significance for the practical development of 'Farmer + Consumer Integration Purchase'.
