TI  - Deep power peak regulation of thermal power-energy storage under high proportion of renewable energy access: based on cooperative game method
AU  - Xie, Tuo
AU  - Chang, Haochen
AU  - Zhang, Gang
AU  - Zhang, Kaoshe
AU  - Qing, Song
T2  - APPLIED THERMAL ENGINEERING
AB  - With the continuous popularization of renewable energy, its inherent volatility and anti-peak shaving characteristics have put forward higher requirements for the peak shaving capacity of modern power systems. To encourage thermal power plants to carry out deep peak shaving, an economic optimal scheduling model of heat storage coupling based on cooperative game theory is proposed for the allocation of deep peak shaving compensation costs. This model consists of three levels: The upper level adopts price-based demand response to minimize net load fluctuations and reduce peak-valley differences; The middle layer optimizes the economic dispatching of thermal power, renewable energy systems and battery energy storage power stations by minimizing the total system cost, maximizing the utilization rate of renewable energy, and enhancing the willingness of power generators to participate in deep peak shaving. The lower layer adopts the cooperative game method based on the Shapley value, combined with the MDP index and the VIKOR method, focusing on maximizing the benefits of the cooperative alliance and the fair distribution of peak shaving compensation costs. The simulation results of the improved IEEE 39-node system show that, compared with the traditional scheduling method, when the penetration rate of renewable energy exceeds 60 %, the total cost of the system decreases by 28.21 %, the abandonment rate of renewable energy decreases by 18.17 %, and the net profit of the system increases by 24.89 %. Compared with the traditional capacity allocation method, The strategy in this paper reduces the shared cost of thermal power by 31.46 %. It has enhanced the flexibility and economy of the power system and provided a fair and reasonable cost-sharing mechanism for compensation. Encourage thermal power units to actively participate in deep peak shaving.
